
{center}
{subhead} NewsRog 1.7 available{def}
{left}
{p} {p}

FOR IMMEDIATE RELEASE
{p} {p}
ShadowWorks Software announces the Version 1.7 update to NewsRog, the
most advanced newsreader available for the Amiga platform.  NewsRog has
a wealth of features for the power user, many of them unavailable in
any other newsreader on any platform.
{p} {p}
Version 1.7 includes 45 new features and improvements, including:
customizable filter toolbars, configurable article filtering for reply
text (or saved/printed article text), the ability to filter threads by
their rate of activity, several new display filters, customizable
filter function toolbars, powerful additions to the built in variable
language, selectable hiding of certain MIME types, updated
documentation, better handling of hanging indents, ISO-8859-X codeset
support, and much more.
{p} {p}
For a full list of other major changes in this version, as well as
descriptions of major NewsRog features and example screenshots, see the
NewsRog preview page at:
{p} {p}
{link http://www.frii.com/~srk/ShadowWorks/Preview/NR.html}http://www.frii.com/~srk/ShadowWorks/Preview/NR.html{end}
{p} {p}
The version 1.7 update is free to registered users as an expression of
thanks to the many loyal NewsRog users who have provided a great deal
of positive feedback and useful suggestions for improving the product.
Version 1.7 may be downloaded from the "Updates" section of the above
web page.
{p} {p}
